ash K, Almhanna K. Total parenteral nutrition for patients with gastrointestinal cancers: a clinical practice review. <em>Ann Palliat Med</em> 2023;12(5):1072–1080.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.21037/apm-22-1380">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37691334/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Total+parenteral+nutrition+for+patients+with+gastrointestinal+cancers%3A+a+clinical+practice+review&amp;author=E+Zametkin&amp;author=D+Guyer&amp;author=Y+Tarshish&amp;author=K+Bash&amp;author=K+Almhanna&amp;publication_year=2023&amp;journal=Ann+Palliat+Med&amp;pages=1072-1080&amp;doi=10.21037%2Fapm-22-1380&amp;pmid=37691334">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">12.</div><div id="r12" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Meyers MA. Radiological features of the spread and localization of extraperitoneal gas and their relationship to its source. An anatomical approach. <em>Radiology</em> 1974;111(1):17–26.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/111.1.17">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/4816102/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Radiological+features+of+the+spread+and+localization+of+extraperitoneal+gas+and+their+relationship+to+its+source.+An+anatomical+approach&amp;author=MA+Meyers&amp;publication_year=1974&amp;journal=Radiology&amp;pages=17-26&amp;doi=10.1148%2F111.1.17&amp;pmid=4816102">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">13.</div><div id="r13" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Meyers MA. 